bug.short_desc: [regression] BuildServerWizardPage gets too wide when expanding sections

long_desc.thetext: If I expand the sections at the bottom of the BuildServerWizardPage, the dialog gets wider. On my vertical monitor, it gets wider than on my horizontal monitor and fills the width of the screen.
Can you attach a screenshot and provide steps to reproduce? I am not able to reproduce this problem on Windows or Linux with the latest.

Created attachment 211283 screenshot
Screenshot showing before (above) and after expanding a section.
Here's what I did just now:
* run on master for all mylyn repositories, on Windows 7, in screen resolution of 1920x1080 (1920x1200 works too), with a clean workspace * open the team repositories view * click add * select Hudson * click to expand Proxy Server Configuration
As I said, the increase in size is much worse on a 1200x1920 (vertical) monitor, but I don't have one available today, and could not reproduce with 1080x1920.
The screenshot shows the expected behavior. The dialog expands its size to the preferred horizontal constraints. If I understand correctly it gets wider than 1200 pixels on a vertical monitor?

It gets as wide as the monitor, which is 1200 pixels, so it looks really bad, and seems like a bug. At 1280x1024, it actually shrinks slightly when the sections are expanded. It doesn't seem like the width needs to change in any of these cases.

Thanks for finding this. There is indeed a snafu in the code. The x and y coordinates are used to set the bounds instead of the width and height of the shell which produces unexpected contraints depending on where the dialog is located on the monitor. Fixed in 9196304288e70af2110da4af830da57e09e0c460.
